{
  "texts": [
    "Observations in the optical are mostly affected by stellar-mass microlenses.",
    "Jiménez-Vicente and Mediavilla (2019) calculate the microlens mean mass of a sample of 24 lensed quasars to be 0.08 < M/M < 0.21 (at 68 per cent confidence) using optical and X-ray flux ratios.",
    "They used fixed-mass simulations and marginalized over all the other free parameters of their model.",
    "Nevertheless, there was still a degeneracy with the source size that was broken by using a size prior from reverberation mapping (Mediavilla et al. 2017).",
    "Using light curve data for Q 2237+0305, Kochanek (2004) and Poindexter and Kochanek (2010) measured 0.006 < M/M < 0.2 and 0.12 < M/M < 1.94 (at 68 per cent confidence) respectively."
  ]
}